<exercise id="fs-id1172098561202">
<problem id="fs-id1172098561204">
<para id="fs-id1172098318082">In a sample of hydrogen sulfide <m:math><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>M</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>34.1</m:mn><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mtext>g/mol</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> at a temperature of <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>3.00</m:mn><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:msup><m:mrow><m:mn>10</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mtext>K</m:mtext><m:mo>,</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> estimate the ratio of the number of molecules that have speeds very close to <m:math><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>v</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mtext>rms</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow></m:math> to the number that have speeds very close to <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:msub><m:mi>v</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mtext>rms</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:msub><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></para>
</problem>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-id1172100675137">
<problem id="fs-id1172100675139">
<para id="fs-id1172098408860">Using the approximation <m:math><m:mrow><m:mstyle displaystyle="true"><m:mrow><m:msubsup><m:mo>∫</m:mo><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>v</m:mi><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:msub></m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>v</m:mi><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mtext>Δ</m:mtext><m:mi>v</m:mi></m:mrow></m:msubsup><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mrow><m:mi>f</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>v</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo><m:mi>d</m:mi><m:mi>v</m:mi><m:mo>≈</m:mo><m:mi>f</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>v</m:mi><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo><m:mtext>Δ</m:mtext><m:mi>v</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:mrow></m:math> for small <m:math><m:mrow><m:mtext>Δ</m:mtext><m:mi>v</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>, estimate the fraction of nitrogen molecules at a temperature of <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>3.00</m:mn><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:msup><m:mrow><m:mn>10</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mtext>K</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math> that have speeds between 290 m/s and 291 m/s.</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-id1172100922647">
<para id="fs-id1172100922649">0.00157</para>
