<exercise id="fs-id1172098267800">
<problem id="fs-id1172098267802">
<para id="fs-id1172100628795">Using the method of the preceding problem, estimate the fraction of nitric oxide (NO) molecules at a temperature of 250 K that have energies between <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>3.45</m:mn><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:msup><m:mrow><m:mn>10</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>−21</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mtext>J</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math> and<m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>3.50</m:mn><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:msup><m:mrow><m:mn>10</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>−21</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mtext>J</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math>.</para>
